# Nix & IaC Orchestration

## Secrets — Non-Negotiable
- **Never** hardcode secrets in Python/Rust/Nix. Use SOPS or `secrets.yaml` ([nix-community/sops-nix Usage](https://github.com/Mic92/sops-nix#usage)).
- Add required system dependencies (e.g., `openssl`, `pkg-config`) to your `devShell`.

## Flake First
- `flake.nix` is the canonical source for package versions ([NixOS Flake Manual](https://nixos.org/manual/nix/stable/command-ref/new-cli/nix3-flake.html)).
- Forbid legacy `shell.nix = import <nixpkgs>` — always use `nix develop`.
- Format Nix code with `nixfmt` ([nixfmt Usage](https://github.com/nix-community/nixfmt#usage)).

## Python in Nix
- Use `uv` + `pyproject.toml` ([Nixpkgs Python packaging guide](https://nixos.org/manual/nixpkgs/stable/#python)).
- Only include: interpreter (`pkgs.python3XX`), `pkgs.uv`, system dependencies.
- Do not use `python3.withPackages` or `pip install`.

## Rust in Nix
- Use `rust-overlay` or `crane` ([crane Nixpkgs docs](https://github.com/ipetkov/crane#nixpkgs-flake-support)) for reproducible builds.

## Discovery Protocol
- **nixos-mcp:** for module/option discovery.
- **nix-locate -w <file>:** find which Nix package provides needed files.
- **rg "services.<name>":** review service/module usage.

**Canonical SOPS:** @InclusiveBlocks/nuc/configuration.nix, @RaspberryPi/hosts/rpi4-01/configuration.nix
**Canonical flake:** @Desktop/flake.nix, @InclusiveBlocks/flake.nix, @RaspberryPi/flake.nix

## Obsidian vault & scope tags
- **Vault paths:** Narrative notes live under `docs/Desktop/` (and may sync to `~/Sync/Obsidian`). They **do not** replace flakes or specs.
- **Scope tags (vault frontmatter):** Align notes with the flake you are changing — e.g. `#scope/desktop` → `Desktop/flake.nix`, `#scope/raspberrypi` → `RaspberryPi/flake.nix`, `#scope/inclusiveblocks` → `InclusiveBlocks/flake.nix`. See `docs/Desktop/reference/obsidian-vault-layout.md`.
- **Secrets in notes:** **Never** paste secret values or decrypted YAML into vault notes. Link to **paths** only (e.g. `RaspberryPi/hosts/rpi4-01/secrets.yaml`), same policy as code.
- **Flake inputs:** Organizing vault folders does **not** add flake inputs; keep **one `nixpkgs`** per repo and `follows` for shared inputs (`sops-nix`, `disko`, etc.).
